Privacy Policy

Effective Date: February 14, 2026

Vibecode Assistant (“the App”) respects your privacy.

Information We Collect

We do not collect, store, or share personal information.
We do not collect analytics, tracking data, or advertising identifiers.
We do not require account creation.
How Your Data Is Used

The App works locally on your device.
Content you create (such as boards, images, and settings) is stored on your device for app functionality.
Clipboard access is only used when you choose features like copy or paste.
Subscriptions and Payments

If you purchase a subscription, payment processing is handled by Apple through the App Store.
We do not receive your full payment details (such as full credit card information).
Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties.
We do not use third-party advertising SDKs.
Children’s Privacy

The App is not designed to collect personal data from anyone, including children.
Data Security

Because data is stored locally on your device, you control your content.
You can delete app data by deleting content in the app or uninstalling the app.
Your Choices

You may stop using the App at any time.
You may manage or cancel subscriptions through your Apple ID subscription settings.
Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this policy in the future.
If updated, the new effective date will be shown at the top.
Contact
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact: betaniagpt@gmail.com
